# Datasets

RADAR-Net is evaluated on four benchmark datasets for rumor detection,
covering two languages, two platforms, and six-fold variation in propagation density.

---

## Dataset Summary

| Dataset | Language | Posts | Rumors | Non-Rumors | Platform | Avg Replies | Split (Train/Val/Test) |
|---------|----------|-------|--------|------------|----------|-------------|------------------------|
| PHEME   | English  | 6,425 | 3,103  | 3,322      | Twitter  | 14.2        | 4,498 / 643 / 1,284    |
| Twitter15 | English | 1,490 | 374   | 578        | Twitter  | 223.4       | 1,043 / 149 / 298      |
| Twitter16 | English | 818  | 205   | 373        | Twitter  | 251.7       | 573 / 82 / 163         |
| Weibo   | Chinese  | 4,664 | 2,313  | 2,351      | Weibo    | 35.6        | 3,264 / 467 / 933      |

Splits are stratified (balanced class distribution in each set).
Propagation graphs truncated at D_max=5 depth and F_max=20 fan-out.
Posts with fewer than 3 replies receive zero-padded virtual silent nodes.

---

## Download Instructions

### PHEME

```bash
# Request access at: https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/PHEME_dataset_for_Rumour_Detection_and_Veracity_Classification/6392078
# Download and extract:
mkdir -p data/raw/pheme
# Place downloaded files in data/raw/pheme/
python data/scripts/preprocess_pheme.py
```

**License:** Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International

### Twitter15 / Twitter16

```bash
# Download from original BiGCN repository:
# https://github.com/TianBian95/BiGCN
mkdir -p data/raw/twitter15 data/raw/twitter16
# Follow instructions in the BiGCN repository README
python data/scripts/preprocess_twitter.py --dataset twitter15
python data/scripts/preprocess_twitter.py --dataset twitter16
```

**License:** See BiGCN repository

### Weibo

```bash
# Available via Ma et al. (2016):
# https://alt.qcri.org/~wgao/data/rumdect.zip
mkdir -p data/raw/weibo
# Place downloaded files in data/raw/weibo/
python data/scripts/preprocess_weibo.py
```

**License:** Research use only

---

## One-Command Download (automated)

```bash
bash scripts/download_datasets.sh
```

This script will download all publicly available datasets and run preprocessing.
Datasets that require manual registration (PHEME) will prompt you with instructions.

---

## Preprocessing

After downloading, run preprocessing to build propagation graphs and tokenize text:

```bash
# Preprocess all datasets
python data/scripts/preprocess.py --dataset all

# Preprocess specific dataset
python data/scripts/preprocess.py --dataset pheme
python data/scripts/preprocess.py --dataset twitter15
python data/scripts/preprocess.py --dataset twitter16
python data/scripts/preprocess.py --dataset weibo
```

Processed data will be saved to `data/processed/` in the following format:

```
data/processed/
├── pheme/
│   ├── train.pt    # torch geometric Data objects
│   ├── val.pt
│   └── test.pt
├── twitter15/
│   ├── train.pt
│   ├── val.pt
│   └── test.pt
├── twitter16/
│   └── ...
└── weibo/
    └── ...
```

---

## Data Format

Each sample is stored as:

```python
{
    "input_ids":      torch.LongTensor,    # (T,) — max T=512 tokens
    "attention_mask": torch.LongTensor,    # (T,)
    "node_features":  torch.FloatTensor,   # (N, 768) — DistilBERT embeddings
    "adj":            torch.FloatTensor,   # (N, N) — normalised adjacency
    "batch_idx":      torch.LongTensor,    # (N,) — node-to-graph mapping
    "label":          int,                 # 0=non-rumour, 1=rumour
    "post_id":        str,
}
```

